<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="503">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181938" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scabriventris Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scabriventris Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scabriventris">scabriventris</taxonomicName>
, rough belly (gaster), referring to the shagreening of the first gastral tergite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="503">
diagnosis Similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181905" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole mixteca Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole mixteca Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixteca">mixteca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181914" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole oaxacana Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole oaxacana Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oaxacana">oaxacana</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181830" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole trageri Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole trageri Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trageri">trageri</taxonomicName>
of Mexico, differing as follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="503">Major: brown, with bluish reflections on first gastral tergite; humerus in dorsal-oblique view raised and subangulate; head quadrate; postpetiolar node from above diamond-shaped; all of anterior half of dorsal head surface carinulate, including clypeus; all of dorsal head surface and of mesosoma foveolate and opaque; anterior two-thirds of central strip of first gastral tergite shagreened and with faint bluish reflections.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="503">Minor: humerus in dorsal-oblique view low and subangulate; postpetiolar node suppressed; pilosity sparse, on mesosomal dorsum consisting of widely and evenly spaced pairs of setae; all of head and mesosoma foveolate and opaque. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.92, HL 0.92, SL 0.50, EL 0.14, PW 0.44. Paratype minor: HW 0.44, HL 0.52, SL 0.46, EL 0.08, PW 0.30.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="503">Color Major: body, mandibles, and most of antennae medium brown; legs brownish yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="503">Minor: body and most of appendages medium brown; tarsi brownish yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="503">Range Known from the type locality, and from Estacion Biologica Los Tuxtlas, Veracruz.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="503">Biology The Los Tuxtlas series was taken from ground litter in rainforest (P. S. Ward) and the holotype series from tropical evergreen forest (S. and J. Peck).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
